      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/no-hits.md",
      "line": 39
    },
    {
      "text": "The truth is that the latch was opened with Rory's spare key.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/no-hits.md",
      "line": 41
    },
    {
      "text": "The room felt still because the HVAC shut down.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/no-hits.md",
      "line": 51
    },
    {
      "text": "The stakes felt real when the board rejected the loan.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/no-hits.md",
      "line": 53
    },
    {
      "text": "She realized the truth when the invoice matched the ledger.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/no-hits.md",
      "line": 55
    },
    {
      "text": "The lesson was simple: rotate the signing key every 30 days.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/no-hits.md",
      "line": 59
    },
    {
      "text": "Fear had no place in the posted evacuation plan because the exits were marked and staffed.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/no-hits.md",
      "line": 61
    },
    {
      "text": "The courtyard smelled of ash because the kiln had cracked during firing.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/no-hits.md",
      "line": 63
    },
    {
      "text": "The wax melted out of the mold because the kiln overheated.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/no-hits.md",
      "line": 65
    },
    {
      "text": "Water washed over the stones after the bucket tipped.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/no-hits.md",
      "line": 67
    },
    {
      "text": "The measured tension settled after the cable was loosened.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/no-hits.md",
      "line": 69
    },
    {
      "text": "Panic rose in her chest because the asthma attack started.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/no-hits.md",
      "line": 71
    },
    {
      "text": "The anger melted out of her posture because the doctor adjusted the brace.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/no-hits.md",
      "line": 73
    },
    {
      "text": "The blur in the photo came from a cracked lens.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/no-hits.md",
      "line": 75
    },
    {
      "text": "The haze over the harbor came from smoke after the warehouse fire.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/no-hits.md",
      "line": 77
    },
    {
      "text": "The rest of the drill was a blur because the camera lens cracked.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/no-hits.md",
      "line": 79
    },
    {
      "text": "Everything after the bell was a haze because smoke filled the hall.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/no-hits.md",
      "line": 81
    },
    {
      "text": "After all, most people expect the process to explain itself.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 41
    },
    {
      "text": "Name the next step, not the whole mountain.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 103
    },
    {
      "text": "“Everyone thinks I sounded stupid” is usually a story, not a fact.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 211
    },
    {
      "text": "Trust erodes, not necessarily because of betrayal, but because the relationship stops feeling like a place where truth can be handled safely.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 219
    },
    {
      "text": "Too much noise, too many demands, too many feelings, not enough room to sort any of it out.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 319
    },
    {
      "text": "If the safest way to survive is to stay quiet, you will get silence, not trust.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 369
    },
    {
      "text": "Silence is not agreement. Silence is often confusion with a nice face on it.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 469
    },
    {
      "text": "They do not fail because people are careless. They fail because the language gets fuzzy at the exact moment clarity matters most.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 471
    },
    {
      "text": "The people most likely to feel attention problems are not mysterious. They are the ones who combine several risk factors at once.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 489
    },
    {
      "text": "The issue is not the number of bodies in the room. It is whether a person feels connected, supported, and seen.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 509
    },
    {
      "text": "Validation is not agreement. It is acknowledging internal logic: \"Given what you heard, it makes sense you felt dismissed.\" When people feel understood, they become more flexible and less defensive.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 585
    },
    {
      "text": "Dishes, lateness, money, or texts are not always about dishes, lateness, money, or texts. They are often stand-ins for deeper themes like reliability, appreciation, fairness, or emotional connection.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 609
    },
    {
      "text": "Adult loneliness is not only the absence of people. It is often the absence of people who know you without explanation.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 615
    },
    {
      "text": "It is not just something you want to do often. It is something your brain learns to initiate with less conscious effort because the cue and the response have been paired repeatedly.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 623
    },
    {
      "text": "Loneliness is not about how many people are around you. It is about whether you feel supported, understood, and safe enough to be real.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 691
    },
    {
      "text": "That is because loneliness is not about how many people are around you. It is about whether you feel seen, safe, and known.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 695
    },
    {
      "text": "The strategy memo is not just a memo. It is a quiet referendum on whether people were right to trust you in the first place.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 715
    },
    {
      "text": "That matters because culture is not an HR initiative. It is the pattern people learn from experience.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 727
    },
    {
      "text": "The best people I know are not the ones who can make everything sound sophisticated. They are the ones who can strip a mess down to its core without needing applause for it.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 737
    },
    {
      "text": "The antidote is not a communication technique. It is the willingness to stay in the room, emotionally, when the impulse is to leave.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 771
    },
    {
      "text": "2/10 The problem is not only how many people are around you. It is whether you feel known, supported, and safe with them.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 793
    },
    {
      "text": "1/10 Loneliness is not just feeling sad in a quieter room. It is what happens when your need for connection is not being met.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 805
    },
    {
      "text": "This is where people get stuck.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 897
    },
    {
      "text": "Some people may generally feel uncertain in some cases.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 901
    },
    {
      "text": "Many adults usually delay the obvious repair.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 903
    },
    {
      "text": "Sixty seconds. That's the whole repair.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 927
    },
    {
      "text": "It was no longer a target. It was noise.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 971
    },
    {
      "text": "The pause was not a delay. It was a warning.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 973
    },
    {
      "text": "She did not wait for anyone to ask her a question. She pointed a small paw toward the ceiling.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 975
    },
    {
      "text": "He didn't argue with the guard. Instead, he opened the ledger.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/hits.md",
      "line": 977
    },
    {
      "text": "The beta endpoint is no longer available. It was removed after the migration.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/no-hits.md",
      "line": 113
    },
    {
      "text": "She did not wait because the clinic was closing.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/no-hits.md",
      "line": 115
    },
    {
      "text": "The status is not final because the review is still open.",
      "family": "syntactic-patterns",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/syntactic-patterns/no-hits.md",
      "line": 117
    },
    {
      "text": "Little did she know, the map had already changed.",
      "family": "narrative-slop",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/narrative-slop/hits.md",
      "line": 47
    },
    {
      "text": "Unbeknownst to him, the signal had failed before dawn.",
      "family": "narrative-slop",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/narrative-slop/hits.md",
      "line": 49
    },
    {
      "text": "Maybe, just maybe, the alley would stay quiet.",
      "family": "narrative-slop",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/narrative-slop/hits.md",
      "line": 51
    },
    {
      "text": "For what seemed like an eternity, the room stayed silent.",
      "family": "narrative-slop",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/narrative-slop/hits.md",
      "line": 53
    },
    {
      "text": "Cassia could not help but feel the alley watching. Her eyes never leaving the shuttered door, she felt a surge of panic.",
      "family": "narrative-slop",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/narrative-slop/hits.md",
      "line": 55
    },
    {
      "text": "Arden couldn't shake the feeling that the mark had moved. A ghost of a smile crossed the guard's face. A dangerous glint flashed in his eyes.",
      "family": "narrative-slop",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/narrative-slop/hits.md",
      "line": 57
    },
    {
      "text": "The report says the phrase \"little did she know\" is a narrative cliche.",
      "family": "narrative-slop",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/narrative-slop/no-hits.md",
      "line": 55
    },
    {
      "text": "The medic could not help but feel the pulse under the bandage.",
      "family": "narrative-slop",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/narrative-slop/no-hits.md",
      "line": 57
    },
    {
      "text": "Cassia stepped onto the marked square, lifted the latch, and checked the number scratched into the brass plate.",
      "family": "narrative-slop",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/narrative-slop/no-hits.md",
      "line": 59
    },
    {
      "text": "Arden looked through the spyhole, counted two guards, and wrote the count on the slate.",
      "family": "narrative-slop",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/narrative-slop/no-hits.md",
      "line": 61
    },
    {
      "text": "Liska's ears flattened under the bandage because the medic wrapped it too tightly.",
      "family": "narrative-slop",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/narrative-slop/no-hits.md",
      "line": 63
    },
    {
      "text": "Remal's tail twitched when the fly landed on the cut.",
      "family": "narrative-slop",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/narrative-slop/no-hits.md",
      "line": 65
    },
    {
      "text": "Marius walked to the rack, picked up the practice sword, and measured it against the broken one.",
      "family": "narrative-slop",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/narrative-slop/no-hits.md",
      "line": 67
    },
    {
      "text": "Cassia watched the pulley until the rope slipped, then marked the frayed strand with chalk.",
      "family": "narrative-slop",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/narrative-slop/no-hits.md",
      "line": 69
    },
    {
      "text": "The actor lowered his voice for the stage cue.",
      "family": "narrative-slop",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/narrative-slop/no-hits.md",
      "line": 71
    },
    {
      "text": "The singer smiled after the conductor gave the entrance cue.",
      "family": "narrative-slop",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/narrative-slop/no-hits.md",
      "line": 73
    },
    {
      "text": "The runner crossed his arms to stretch his shoulders before the race.",
      "family": "narrative-slop",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/narrative-slop/no-hits.md",
      "line": 75
    },
    {
      "text": "The technician rested her hands on the sill to reach the loose antenna cable.",
      "family": "narrative-slop",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/narrative-slop/no-hits.md",
      "line": 77
    },
    {
      "text": "Cassia's throat went tight before she could answer.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/hits.md",
      "line": 197
    },
    {
      "text": "For a moment, her eyes moved from the window to the floor.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/hits.md",
      "line": 199
    },
    {
      "text": "Her eyes moved from the window to the floor because the chalk mark continued under the sill.",
      "family": "semantic-thinness",
      "bucket": "no-hits",
      "source": "cases/semantic-thinness/no-hits.md",
      "line": 187
    },
    {
      "text": "She did not answer the guard because the bell drowned out his question.",
